libsklog - Make secure logging using Schneier and Kelsey scheme
===============================================================

	Copyright (C) 2007-2010 Politecnico di Torino, Italy
	TORSEC group -- http://security.polito.it

Libsklog is a library for C language that makes possible the
generation of log entries by following the scheme defined by
B.Schneier ad J.Kelsey in "Secure Audit Logs to Support
Computer Forensics".

Installation notes
------------------

1) Prerequisites

    OpenSSL >= 0.9.8
    SQLite 3.x
	libtool
	autotool

2) Building

    $> tar zxvf libsklog-VERSION.tar.gz
    $> cd ./libsklog-VERSION
	$> mkdir m4
    $> autoreconf --install
    $> ./configure --prefix=/usr/local
    $> make
    $> make install (as root)
    
    You can add to ./configure the options "--enable-trace" to build the
    library in high verbosity mode and "--enable-quote" to build the library
    with the TPM_Quote support. For more information run
    
    $> ./configure --help
    
